In 1998 Amanda Lear misguidedly decided to re-record nine of her best known songs from the disco era for album/compilation ''[[Back In Your Arms]]'', namely "These Boots Are Made For Walking", "Follow Me", "The Sphinx", "Tomorrow" (2 versions), "Enigma (Give A Bit Of Mmh To Me)", "Queen Of Chinatown", "Fashion Pack (Studio 54)", "Blood And Honey" and "Fabulous Lover Love Me". The album was produced and issued by minor Italian label Dig-It International and only met with limited critical and commercial success on its initial release.<br />
